0000008930712, 
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEBFFA8FF152E37FE8FF8EF" box="[136,294,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of the original materials of Comolia berberifolia (Bonpl.) DC. A. Lectotype at P (P00482343). B–D. Details of isolectotype at BR (BR0000008930712). B. Isolectotype with original draft description in the background and the fragment of the type. C. Detail of sketch of the original illustration. D. Fragment of the type. E. Draft description prepared by Cogniaux with the isolectotype at BR. Sources: ©Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, P00482343. Available in: http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/ p/p00482343. ©National Botanic Garden of Belgium, Meise Botanic Garden, Meise, BR0000008930712. Available in: http://www. botanicalcollections.be/specimen/BR0000008930712." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Figures 2B–E</figureCitation>
), with a sheet containing a sketch of the original illustration and description (
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEBFFA8FBE22E37FA89F8EF" box="[1151,1312,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of the original materials of Comolia berberifolia (Bonpl.) DC. A. Lectotype at P (P00482343). B–D. Details of isolectotype at BR (BR0000008930712). B. Isolectotype with original draft description in the background and the fragment of the type. C. Detail of sketch of the original illustration. D. Fragment of the type. E. Draft description prepared by Cogniaux with the isolectotype at BR. Sources: ©Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, P00482343. Available in: http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/ p/p00482343. ©National Botanic Garden of Belgium, Meise Botanic Garden, Meise, BR0000008930712. Available in: http://www. botanicalcollections.be/specimen/BR0000008930712." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Figures 2B–C</figureCitation>
), a fragment of the type (
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEBFFA8FE852E53FE45F8B2" box="[280,492,1862,1889]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of the original materials of Comolia berberifolia (Bonpl.) DC. A. Lectotype at P (P00482343). B–D. Details of isolectotype at BR (BR0000008930712). B. Isolectotype with original draft description in the background and the fragment of the type. C. Detail of sketch of the original illustration. D. Fragment of the type. E. Draft description prepared by Cogniaux with the isolectotype at BR. Sources: ©Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, P00482343. Available in: http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/ p/p00482343. ©National Botanic Garden of Belgium, Meise Botanic Garden, Meise, BR0000008930712. Available in: http://www. botanicalcollections.be/specimen/BR0000008930712." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Figures 2B and D</figureCitation>
), and a draft of the description of 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEBFFA8FC1F2E53FBE4F8B3" box="[898,1101,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Flora brasiliensis</emphasis>
prepared by 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEBFFA8FB772E53FA02F8B2" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[1258,1451,1862,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" refId="ref8702" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Melastomaceae. Tribus II. Tibouchineae Baill. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas. Vol. 14. Frid. Fleischer, Monachii et Lipsiae [Munich &amp; Leipzig], pp. 205 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book" year="1885">Cogniaux (1885)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEBFFA8FF0D2E7FFEAEF857" box="[144,263,1898,1924]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of the original materials of Comolia berberifolia (Bonpl.) DC. A. Lectotype at P (P00482343). B–D. Details of isolectotype at BR (BR0000008930712). B. Isolectotype with original draft description in the background and the fragment of the type. C. Detail of sketch of the original illustration. D. Fragment of the type. E. Draft description prepared by Cogniaux with the isolectotype at BR. Sources: ©Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, P00482343. Available in: http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/ p/p00482343. ©National Botanic Garden of Belgium, Meise Botanic Garden, Meise, BR0000008930712. Available in: http://www. botanicalcollections.be/specimen/BR0000008930712." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEBFFA8FE812E7FFE52F857" author="Rocha, M. J. R. &amp; Guimaraes, P. J. F. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Batista, J. A. N." box="[284,507,1898,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" pagination="50 - 74" refId="ref10431" refString="Rocha, M. J. R., Guimaraes, P. J. F., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Batista, J. A. N. (2018) Taxonomy of Marcetieae: A new neotropical tribe of Melastomataceae. International Journal of Plant Sciences 179: 50 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 694932" type="journal article" year="2018">
Rocha 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEBFFA8FEF02E7EFE09F857" box="[365,416,1898,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned the duplicate at 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FCEC2E7EFC30F856" box="[881,921,1899,1925]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">BR</collectionCode>
, however considered mistakenly the specimen at 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FF392E9AFF1AF87A" box="[164,179,1935,1961]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
as the 
<typeStatus id="131A8869FFEBFFA8FE9F2E9BFECEF87B" box="[258,359,1934,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">holotype</typeStatus>
, because these are 
<typeStatus id="131A8869FFEBFFA8FDA02E9AFD0AF87A" box="[573,675,1935,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Since the sketch of the original illustration is on the sheet at 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FACA2E9AFAD6F87A" box="[1367,1407,1935,1961]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">BR</collectionCode>
, we interpret that this material composes the original material. Thus, typification is necessary (see Article 9.3 of the 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FAEF2EA7FA0DF81F" box="[1394,1444,1970,1996]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">ICN</collectionCode>
) and here we consider 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEBFFA8FEE12EC2FDE9F823" box="[380,576,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FEE12EC2FE38F822" box="[380,401,2007,2033]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FE082EC2FE00F822" box="[405,425,2007,2033]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">R</collectionCode>
. Ferreira s.n.
</emphasis>
deposited at 
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FD482EC2FD4DF822" box="[725,740,2007,2033]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
(
<collectionCode id="AAB0AE0EFFEBFFA8FD6F2EC3FCABF823" box="[754,770,2006,2032]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
00482343, 
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEBFFA8FC1F2EC3FC5FF823" box="[898,1014,2006,2032]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[242,1345,190,1842]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of the original materials of Comolia berberifolia (Bonpl.) DC. A. Lectotype at P (P00482343). B–D. Details of isolectotype at BR (BR0000008930712). B. Isolectotype with original draft description in the background and the fragment of the type. C. Detail of sketch of the original illustration. D. Fragment of the type. E. Draft description prepared by Cogniaux with the isolectotype at BR. Sources: ©Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, P00482343. Available in: http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/ p/p00482343. ©National Botanic Garden of Belgium, Meise Botanic Garden, Meise, BR0000008930712. Available in: http://www. botanicalcollections.be/specimen/BR0000008930712." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
) as the 
<typeStatus id="131A8869FFEBFFA8FBD12EC3FB1FF823" box="[1100,1206,2006,2032]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
